<Task/><Text-field style="Heading 1" layout="Heading 1">Documentation to PointGroups package</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">PointGroups is a package for in-depth use of point groups.</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">To install the package run the code in the corresponding section below<Hyperlink linktarget="Wks:install.mw" hyperlink="true"></Hyperlink>.</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">Actually you need not to install the package, just</Text-field>
<Group labelreference="L3" drawlabel="true">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">read &quot;PointGroups.ini&quot;;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Hyperlink linktarget="Help:FiniteGroups" hyperlink="true"><Font underline="true" style="Normal">FiniteGroups</Font></Hyperlink> package is required.</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">The author is Andriy Zhugayevych, azh@ukr.net.</Text-field><Text-field style="Heading 2" layout="Heading 2">Notations and basic data types</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">g,h</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 </Font>group element</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">p</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 </Font>point of a linear space where the group acts
<Font style="Code">G,H::list(g)</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 group</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">S::list(g)</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 any set of elements</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">preS::list(g)</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 repeating elements are allowed</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Heading 2" layout="Heading 2">Representations of predefined groups</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">To define a group create the following Group Record:</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">GR::Record(</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code"> 'name'::string,</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 group name (all the strings below may be empty)</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code"> 'namegen'::list of string,</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 names of generators</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code"> 'gen'::list,</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 generators (unit element may be not included if </Font><Font style="Code">gen[1]^0=e</Font>)</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code"> 'GF'::proc(gen) of G,</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 function generating the group, elements ordering must not depend on generators</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code"> 'nameC'::list of string,</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 names of conjugacy classes</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code"> 'GFC'::proc(gen) of S,</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 function generating representatives of conjugacy classes</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code"> 'NC'::list of posint,</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 list of the numbers of elements in conjugacy classes</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code"> 'nameR'::list of string,</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 names of irreducible representations</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code"> 'genR'::list of list of Matrix):</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 generators of irreducible representations corresponding to </Font><Font style="Code">gen</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">FG_ChTb(GR,{fulloutput::boolean:=false})::Matrix</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 builds character table of a given matrix group, if </Font><Font style="Code">fulloutput</Font> returns also labels for representations and conjugacy classes</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">FG_RepU(R0,R)::list(Matrix)</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 for any representation </Font><Font style="Code">R0</Font> returns the list of matrices <Font style="Code">U</Font> of unitary transformation to irreducible representation <Font style="Code">R</Font>, so that <Font style="Code">HermitianTranspose(U).R0.U=R</Font>. Note that <Font style="Code">R0</Font> and <Font style="Code">R</Font> must have the same ordering. See also <Font style="Code">FG_RepU2</Font> in source file</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">FG_RepDec(R,GR)::list([string,list(Matrix)])</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 decompose representation </Font><Font style="Code">R</Font> into irreducible representations of <Font style="Code">GR</Font>, the result is a list of names and matrices of unitary transformation of irreducible representations</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">FG_Ch(R,GR)::list(nonnegint)</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 returns the characters of elements in </Font><Font style="Code">R</Font> corresponding to conjugacy classes representatives</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">FG_RepDecCh(chi::list,ChTb::Matrix,NC::list)::list(nonnegint)</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 short form of the decomposition of any representation given by its characters </Font><Font style="Code">chi</Font> into irreducible representation of a group given by its character table <Font style="Code">ChTb</Font> and list <Font style="Code">NC</Font> of the numbers of elements in conjugacy classes, the result is a list of irreducible representations numbers</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">FG_indexC(GR)::list(nonnegint)</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 returns the list of indexes of conjugacy classes representatives generated by </Font><Font style="Code">GR:-GFC</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">FG_dimR(GR)::list(nonegint)</Font> <Font encoding="UTF-8">\342\200\223 returns the list of dimensions of irreducible representations</Font></Text-field>
<Group labelreference="L58188" drawlabel="true">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">with(FiniteGroups): with(PointGroups):
HT:=LinearAlgebra[HermitianTranspose]:
<Font encoding="UTF-8">myRank:=M-&gt;`i\134f`(nops(op(2,M))&gt;0,LinearAlgebra[Rank](M),0):
</Font>svf:=[seq(map(FG_simplify,simplify(ReflectionM(map(convert,&lt;sin(Pi/2/n),cos(Pi/2/n),0&gt;,radical)))),n=1..6)]:
PGrepdim:=s-&gt;piecewise(s[1]=&quot;A&quot; or s[1]=&quot;B&quot;,1,s[1]=&quot;E&quot;,2,s[1]=&quot;F&quot; or s[1]=&quot;T&quot;,3,s[1]=&quot;G&quot;,4,s[1]=&quot;H&quot;,5,undefined):
unassign('x,y,z,a,b,c');</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="HyperlinkWarning" layout="HyperlinkWarning"><Hyperlink linktarget="http://www.maplesoft.com/support/help/errors/view.aspx?path=Warning,%20Use%20'matrix'%20instead%20of%20'Matrix'" hyperlink="true"><Font style="HyperlinkWarning">Warning, Use 'matrix' instead of 'Matrix'</Font></Hyperlink></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L58842" drawlabel="true">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
